  <abstract>Plain postal card addressed to sender's mother, Mrs. E. A. Roller. John writes from Camp Sevier, South Carolina, that he "received the note and $2 papa sent." He reports that he is "getting along all OK," and that he had received letters from relatives. John Roller in HQ Co., 115th FA., 30th Div. The 30th Div. was composed of North and South Carolina and Tennessee National Guard units and was created at Camp Sevier, South Carolina in 1917. They served with the British throughout the fighting in France.</abstract>
